Subject: [ghostium] Navigator webdriver + deviceMemory hook anchor

Spec-E wiring. Anchors at top of ``navigator.cc``. The real call into
``FingerprintNoiseSource::WebDriverOverride`` lands inside the
``Navigator::webdriver()`` getter (default-false when a profile is
present, upstream default otherwise), and the real call into
``DeviceMemoryOverride`` lands inside ``Navigator::deviceMemory()``
(returning the rounded GiB value the profile carries).

Both surfaces share this single navigator.cc anchor so the two
patches do not collide on the file's top-of-file marker line range.

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
@@ -20,7 +20,15 @@
  *  Foundation, Inc., 51 Franklin Street, Fifth Floor, Boston,
  *  MA 02110-1301, USA
  */
 
+// GHOSTIUM-HOOK-ANCHOR: Spec-E navigator.cc surfaces.
+//   * Navigator::webdriver() consults
+//     FingerprintNoiseSource::WebDriverOverride.
+//   * Navigator::deviceMemory() consults
+//     FingerprintNoiseSource::DeviceMemoryOverride.
+//   See
+//   //ghostium_src/overlay/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/ghostium_fp/fingerprint_noise_source.h
+//   and plan.md sections 4.6 / 4.7.
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.h"
 
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/bindings/core/v8/script_controller.h"
